A) 🔴 NEW (2026-06-13) — **dev CI is RED**: `pytest --strict-markers` hard-errors collecting `tests/test_mermaid_dogfood.py` (`@pytest.mark.mermaid`) + `tests/test_mermaid_e2e.py` (`@pytest.mark.mermaid_mcp`) because those 2 markers are NOT registered in `pyproject.toml`'s `markers` list. Latent: normally an env pytest plugin registers them, but its install is flaking → all craft CI fails when it does. **Fix (tiny, root-cause):** add `mermaid` + `mermaid_mcp` to the `markers = [...]` block in `pyproject.toml` (~line 23–53). Do via worktree → PR to dev. Closes the fragility for good; no more `--admin` bypasses needed.
